    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I prefer using the Calendar object.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Calendar now = GregorianCalendar.getInstance()\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I find it much easier to work with.  You can also get a Date object from the Calendar.  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/GregorianCalendar.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/GregorianCalendar.html</a></p>\n"
